{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fd63cc53-3ec3-4883-bbab-7b99a39c4401","content":"Here's a complete migration plan for moving 5 MSTest projects from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP).\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1 — Update NuGet packages\n\nIn each test `.csproj`, replace the three legacy packages with a single unified one:\n\n**Remove:**\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"17.13.0\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest.TestAdapter\" Version=\"3.8.0\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest.TestFramework\" Version=\"3.8.0\" />\n```\n\n**Add:**\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.0\" />\n```\n\nThe `MSTest` meta-package (≥ 3.4) includes the runner, framework, and SDK. The two older `MSTest.*` packages and `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` are no longer needed.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2 — Enable MTP runner\n\nAdd to each test project (or a shared `Directory.Build.props`):\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n  <!-- Keep vstest compatibility during transition (opt-in) -->\n  <!-- <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport> -->\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n`EnableMSTestRunner` makes each test project a self-contained executable. `OutputType` must be `Exe`.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 3 — Validate locally\n\n```bash\n# Build all projects\ndotnet build\n\n# Run with the new runner directly\ndotnet run --project tests/MyTests1/MyTests1.csproj\n\n# Or via dotnet test (uses compatibility layer in MSTest ≥ 3.4)\ndotnet test\n```\n\nEach test project is now an executable. You can run it directly (`./MyTests1`) or via `dotnet test`, which invokes MTP under the hood.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 4 — TRX reporting\n\nMTP doesn't emit TRX by default. Add the TRX report extension:\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\" Version=\"1.6.2\" />\n```\n\nWhen running directly, enable with `--report-trx`. Via `dotnet test`, add:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- --report-trx --report-trx-filename TestResults.trx\n```\n\n---\n\n## Phase 5 — Code coverage\n\nReplace any legacy `Microsoft.CodeCoverage` or `coverlet` setup. For MTP, use:\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage\" Version=\"17.13.0\" />\n```\n\nRun with:\n```bash\ndotnet test -- --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura\n```\n\n---\n\n## Phase 6 — Azure DevOps pipeline changes\n\nReplace the `VSTest@3` task with `DotNetCoreCLI@2`:\n\n**Before:**\n```yaml\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testAssemblyVer2: '**\\*Tests.dll'\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n```\n\n**After:**\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run Tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: '-- --report-trx --report-trx-filename TestResults.trx --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura'\n\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest   # TRX format\n    testResultsFiles: '**/TestResults.trx'\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '**/coverage.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n---\n\n## Phase 7 — Cleanup\n\n- Remove any remaining references to `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`, `MSTest.TestAdapter`, or `MSTest.TestFramework`.\n- Remove `.runsettings` files if they only configured VSTest-specific options (adapter paths, etc.). Any test-filtering or parallelism settings move to MSTest config or CLI args.\n- Delete the old `VSTest@3` task definition from your pipeline YAML.\n\n---\n\n## Rollout strategy\n\nMigrate **one project at a time**. Run it in parallel with the old pipeline definition until green, then proceed to the next. The key risk areas are:\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|---|---|\n| Custom `.runsettings` | Translate to MTP CLI args or `[assembly:]` attributes |\n| `DeploymentItem` / data files | Verify `CopyToOutputDirectory` still works as Exe |\n| Ordered tests | MTP doesn't support `.orderedtest`; refactor to `[TestMethod]` with explicit ordering |\n| Test filters (`/TestCaseFilter`) | Use `--filter` with same syntax |\n\nTackle one project, validate CI end-to-end (tests + TRX + coverage), then repeat for the remaining four.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8e0c4aa9-f93b-4405-b8ea-5714a749435c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The repository appears to be empty. The user is asking for a migration plan, not asking me to perform the migration on an existing codebase. Let me provide a comprehensive migration plan based on my knowledge of migrating from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) with MSTest.\n\nLet me provide a thorough, structured migration plan.","outputTokens":1328,"requestId":"4C15:3F94EE:DEBA9A:113D0B6:6A012B7C"},"id":"d2842264-5349-4544-ba17-aceaeaee42a5","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:06:32.133Z","parentId":"4c3c8d11-295e-448f-be29-b632300fb025"}
